Johannesburg Two members of the SA National Defence Force (SANDF) died on Thursday when their military truck collided with two other trucks near Makhado, Limpopo police said.&quot;The accident happened along the N1 north next to Hartleigh, 46km North of Makhado. It is alleged the two trucks, of which one was a military truck, were travelling towards Makhado when another truck travelling towards the north lost control and collided with the two,&quot; said spokesman Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo. One of the SANDF members died at the scene and the other died on arrival at hospital. Police were investigating a case of culpable homicide. African News Agency